H0.text: Underside is where the mouth opening is located on a jellyfish.

H1.text: The left side is where the mouth opening is located on a jellyfish.

H2.text: The mouth opening on a jellyfish is located on the right side.

H3.text: The mouth opening on a jellyfish is located on the top.

A4.text: The mouth opens into a central stomach.

A5.text: The mouth opens into a central stomach, from which four interconnected diverticula radiate outwards.

A6.text: At its tip is the mouth.
